I '''Qin Shi Huang''' ({{zh-cpw|c=秦始皇|p=Qín Shǐhuáng|w=Ch'in Shih-huang}}) (259 BCE – 210 BCE),<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.travelchinaguide.com/attraction/shaanxi/xian/terra_cotta_army/qin_shihuang_1.htm |title=Emperor Qin Shi Huang -- First Emperor of China |publisher=TravelChinaGuide.com |accessdate=2007-09-10 }}</ref><ref name="Wood1">Wood, Frances. (2008). China's First Emperor and His Terracotta Warriors. Macmillan publishing. ISBN 0-312-38112-3, 9780312381127. p 2.</ref> lagiu '''Ying Zheng''' ({{zh-cp|c=嬴政|p=Yíng Zhèng}}), metung yang ari ra reng Isik keng [[Qin (state)|State na ning Qin]] manibat 246 BCE anggang 221 BCE inyang  [[Warring States Period]].<ref name="duik">Duiker, William J. Spielvogel, Jackson J. Edition: 5, illustrated. (2006). World History: Volume I: To 1800. Thomson Higher Education publishing. ISBN 0-495-05053-9, 9780495050537. pg 78.</ref> Iya ing minunang emperador ning pisanmetung a Tsina inyang 221 BCE.<ref name="duik" /> Menungkulan ya anggang inyang king kayang kakamtayan inyang 210 BCE king idad a  50.<ref name="Ren">Ren, Changhong. Wu, Jingyu. (2000). Rise and Fall of Qin Dynasty. Asiapac Books Pte Ltd. ISBN 981-229-172-5, 9789812291721.</ref>

I Qin Shi Huangdi kaibat neng pisanmetung ing Tsina, iya at ing kayang manimunang talausuk i [[Li Si]] pepalual lang reforma keng politica ampong pang economia.<ref name="duik" /> Megmandu yang magaragula projectu, kayabe ne ing mumunang dake ning [[Great Wall ning China]], at ngeni ing bantug a sukad lakanbalen a [[Mausoleum of the First Qin Emperor|mausoleum]] a nung nu deng terra cotta sundalus ial deng makabante.  Para a siguradu na ing kataimikan i Qin Shi Huang binawal no reng  [[Confucianism]] ampong [[Burning of books and burying of scholars|kikut nong mabie deng scholars]].<ref name="Ren" />  Agiang maigpit ya keng kayang pamanungkulan mekilala ya i Qin Shi Huang bilang metung keng migpabayu keng Tsina.

